This paper deals with the security of healthcare applications, which involves protecting sensitive patient data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of Elliptic Curve Cryptography and PHOTON, which are commonly used in secure communication protocols, indicating that cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on healthcare applications, suggesting that cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category. Finally, the paper proposes a new authentication model, indicating that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a possible category.
